Tries to read some bytes directly into the given `buf` in asynchronous

defs.name: Read
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read available number of bytes to fill
 a buffer.

defs.name: ReadExact
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read exactly enough bytes to fill
 a buffer.

defs.name: read_exact
defs.value: fn <A, T> (a: A, buf: T) -> ReadExact<A, T>
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will read exactly enough bytes to fill `buf`,

defs.name: ReadToEnd
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read the entire contents of a stream
 into a vector.

defs.name: read_to_end
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will read all the bytes associated with the I/O
 object `A` into the buffer provided.

defs.name: ReadUntil
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read the contents of a stream into a
 vector until the delimiter is reached.

defs.name: read_until
defs.value: fn <A> (a: A, byte: u8, buf: Vec<u8>) -> ReadUntil<A>
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will read all the bytes associated with the I/O
 object `A` into the buffer provided until the delimiter `byte` is reached.
 This method is the async equivalent to [`BufRead::read_until`].

defs.name: Shutdown
defs.docs: A future used to fully shutdown an I/O object.

defs.name: shutdown
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will entirely shutdown an I/O object and then yield
 the object itself.

defs.name: WriteAll
defs.docs: A future used to write the entire contents of some data to a stream.

defs.name: write_all
defs.value: fn <A, T> (a: A, buf: T) -> WriteAll<A, T>
defs.docs:
Creates a future that will write the entire contents of the buffer `buf` to
 the stream `a` provided.
